# .trivyignore — accepted Trivy findings.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line, plus optional "# rationale" comment above it.
# Only add entries with a documented reason the finding is being accepted.
# Example:
#   # CVE-2024-XXXX: only reachable via feature we don't use; upstream fix pending
#   CVE-2024-XXXX
#
# Policy: critical/high findings must not be silenced — fix them or upgrade.
# Medium findings accepted only after chainability review.
# Low findings may be accepted with rationale.
